span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">c</span>, <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">d</span>, are real number=
s, and <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>i</b></span>, <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>=
j</b></span>, <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>k</b></span>, are <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symbol_(mathematics)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Symbol (mathematics)">symbols</a> that can be interpreted as unit-vecto=
rs pointing along the three spatial axes. In practice, if one of <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span>, <span class=3D"te=
xhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml m=
var" style=3D"font-style:italic;">c</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" st=
