trices in such a way that quaternion addition and multiplication correspond=
 to matrix addition and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matrix_mul=
tiplication" title=3D"Matrix multiplication">matrix multiplication</a>. One=
 is to use 2 =C3=97 2 complex matrices, and the other is to use 4 =C3=97 4 =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_number" title=3D"Real number"=
>real</a> matrices. In each case, the representation given is one of a fami=
ly of linearly related representations. These are <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Injective_function" title=3D"Injective function">injective<=
/a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring_homomorphism" title=3D"Ri=
ng homomorphism">homomorphisms</a> from <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe=
-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml=
-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/=
